A good morning bagel place! They have a wide variety of options. We got the onion bagel tuna salad and a bacon egg and cheese. The bacon one needed a little more salt but the onion bagel was quite tasty. The tuna salad tastes fresh and the veggies are also quite refreshing.
Love the bagels here. Super fresh and have a lovely selection. Very nice twists on some old fashioned bagels as well. Definetly recommend trying the "My Ex" bagel!

Best bagels on the Upper West Side! We’ve been eating here for more than 15 years - including a years-long stretch where our kids insisted on a Sunday morning visit for their faves every week. We’re partial to the Everything bagel, toasted, with scallion cream cheese and lox. And to the My-Ex with whitefish salad. Their tuna salad is terrific, too. The staff members are friendly and super efficient. During the pandemic, it’s takeout only.

We actually did a blind taste test with a group of family members and the everything bagel from Lenny’s, Absolute, and Broadway Bagel (not in the same league, but we needed a third), and Lenny’s won pretty handily. Bonus: no crazy line like Absolute.  My favorite is the Bad Boy: egg bagel with garlic, onion, and poppy seed. The scallion cream cheese is also nice and zingy.  Pre- and post-COVID: line up on the right along the cold cases to order, move over to the left by the drinks to wait. There is no line to get into on the left.

It's well priced if you factor in their crazy "Buy this and get this" policies which are hard to follow. (Buy dozen bagels get 2 free. Buy 1/4 lb salmon get 2 bagels free, etc etc). Great fresh whitefish, tuna, egg salad  Real neighborhood find.
You will be disappointed. The texture of cream cheese on my bagel resembled sand and the lox came with scales still attached.

I had an unfortunate incident at Lennys yesterday where I had bought a breakfast sandwich and a tea. I was walking home and the paper bag had broke and came back to get another tea only to find out they would charge me an additional cost of 2.50 plus another item to fulfill the 5.00 minimum threshold for debit cards. In complete shock I had asked the employee there why I am being charged and he rather shrugged his shoulders and he looked at the manager only for her to say to me rudely “It’s your fault”. If the manager or owner reads this as a longtime customer of 25 years I’d like to have a complementary tea in compensation for very poor customer service. Otherwise, my family and I will no longer be doing business with you.

I visited Lenny's with two needs: to eat and use the bathroom.  The bathroom is in the basement and was not a disaster. The food was excellent and the hot sauce made me think about my friends ex girlfriend who I always kind of liked.  The staff was polite and kind and when the man gave me my bag of food he reassured me that the coffee was in the bag as well, which soothed my fears about where is my coffee.  I got cookies too and they were good and very reasonably priced.  I wish more places were like Lenny's thank you lenny's long live Lenny's.

Strawberry Marshmallows-made with real strawberries! You can actually taste the seeds! Cinnamon Pecan Marshmallows-infused with cinnamon and a candied pecan placed on top Coconut Marshmallows-rolled in toasted coconut flakes Vanilla Marshmallows-original flavor, and it tastes even better than the marshmallows of my younger years Smores-graham cracker topped with vanilla marshmallow covered in dark chocolate Peanut Butter Smore-same as a regular smore except with a layer of peanut butter in the middle. So good! Coconut macaroons Homemade Graham Crackers-made with whole wheat flower and super flaky and delicious  They have other items to offer as well but these are the only items I have tried so far, and I love them all! Every once in awhile S&S will also offer discounted mallows and smores. They taste exactly the same except they are just odd shaped leftovers or mess ups from the kitchen. But I don't care they still taste awesome.  The only thing about ordering online that's a bit sucky is the amount of shipping that's charged. It can get expensive depending on the amount of items you buy and whether or not you need hot weather insulation for your items so they don't melt. I will probably wait until winter to order again so that way I can scale back on the amount of shipping I need to pay. But you know what, its way better than buying the cheap marshmallows in the store filled with gelatin. So the prices are way justifiable in my opinion. You don't even have to be a vegetarian to love these mallows. Try them. They won't disappoint!

This was my neighborhood bagel shop for years, but having tried all the best regarded places in nyc (Absolute, H&H, Murray's, Best), Lenny's is #1. Definitely wasn't cheap for a sandwich, but pretty good. They had a lot of options, for sure. I opted for the Jimmy T, which was a chicken cutlet with melted mozzarella cheese, grilled onion, sweet peppers and honey mustard. Mmmmm. Quite good. They had a full selection of yogurt muffins, which sounded like a must check out breakfast option. It wasn't until ordering that I saw their "Steam Table" options. Fresh oven roasted turkey, Meat loaf, Fresh corned beef brisket, Grilled chicken breast, Herb chicken, or Grilled salmon... mmmmm. And possibility to have mac as a side. Will be back to give that a go for sure.
